.SH "ESCAPE HANDLING"
Commands that take more than one character of input (s, w, P, N, etc) accept
the full set of rn-like %-escapes documented in
.IR newsreaders (5).
Typing %% while answering a query from one of these commands will force
escape expansion of the text in the buffer so far.
.PP
The %m (mode, see newsreaders(5) for details) escape has the following values:
.PD 0
.TP 10
"A"
when the reader is displaying an article
.TP 10
"S"
when the reader is displaying a subject list
.TP 10
"G"
when the reader is displaying a group list
.TP 10
"H"
when the reader is displaying a help filw
.TP 10
"I"
during initialization, before an article has been seen.
.PP
The %V escape has the value "vnews".
