.SH NOTE
There have been significant changes to vnews for TMN-netnews.
Most readers will probably want to use the new -S option.
The "options [reader] ..." feature of .newsrc files is new.
The behavior of the - command is very different.
The ! command now recognizes the & and | final chars
and sets the $A environment variable). The F, g, l, ^, & and ud commands
and the group-list and subject-index modes are new.
The semantics of s and w have changed slightly, becoming more rn-like. To get
the old behavior, set NEWSDIR="." in your environment
The -c and -h options have been replaced by -p modes; defaults for -p have
been set to serve today's faster tty devices. 
